The remains of former Zimbabwean president Robert Mugabe are being repatriated. Mugabe died in Singapore on Friday. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The remains of Zimbabwe's ex-president Robert Mugabe have arrived in Harare on Wednesday. The 95-year-old statesman died in a Singapore hospital on Friday. Mugabe's body will be received by President Emmerson Mnangagwa. READ: Robert Mugabe dies aged 95 His body will lie in state on Thursday and Friday to allow the public to pay their last respects. Mugabe's funeral is expected to take place on Sunday. His burial atÂ Heroe's Acre is still being contested. Many foreign dignitaries will be attending former Zimbabwean president Robert Mugabe's funeral. Courtesy #DStv403